=== TASK ===
# Ticket Board

## Overview
Build a feature-rich, Kanban-style Ticket Board within LifeOps that enables teams to manage issues/tickets with dynamic agent automation rules, bulk edit capabilities, and sprint planning tools. This page sits at the core of Project Management Automation (roadmaps, ticketing automation, PR summarization, release notes, CI/CD integrations via agents) and is tightly integrated with the Project Detail view (backlog, roadmap items, tickets, PRs, agent-run history, and action widgets). The UI must be performant, accessible, and resilient to null/undefined data, with strong runtime safety guarantees as specified in the mandatory coding standards.

## Page Description (Full Detail)
What this page is:
- A comprehensive Kanban board for tickets within a project, featuring multiple lanes (columns) such as Backlog, Ready, In Progress, In Review, Done, and custom/status-based lanes.
- An Agent Automation Rules Panel to define and manage rules that triage, assign, tag, escalate, or auto-resolve tickets based on ticket attributes, events, or agent state.
- A Sprint Planner to allocate tickets to sprints, visualize capacity, and drag tickets into sprint columns; includes capacity indicators per sprint and per-team/resource constraints.
- Bulk Actions to perform multi-ticket edits (change status, assign, tag, priority, estimate, convert to tasks, bulk PR summarization notes, etc.).
- Tight integration with Roadmaps and CI/CD workflows via agents, enabling automated ticket routing to automation templates, PR summarization, release notes generation, and deployment steps.
- Auditability: every action is explainable, reversible, and logged with traceable agent messages, consistent with LifeOps governance.

How this page should look and behave:
- A dense yet readable Kanban board with draggable tickets between columns, inline quick-edit, and bulk operation controls.
- Left-hand side: collapsible navigation tree and filter panel for projects, teams, assignees, labels, and sprint contexts.
- Top header: project context, sprint selector, quick actions (Create Ticket, Create Automation Rule, Run Summary), search, and global filters.
- Right-side: Agent Automation Rules Panel with create/edit rule UI, preview of rule effects, and a history of rule executions.
- Sprint planner dock: an integrated panel showing active sprint(s), capacity, and a draggable area to assign cards to sprints.
- Cards: dark elevated with rounded corners, top-aligned priority icon or badge, title, assignees, tags, due date, and a compact bottom bar with status, points, and last updated times.
- Interactions: drag-and-drop tickets across columns; bulk select with a persistent action toolbar; modal dialogs for editing ticket details; in-place quick edits; confirm prompts for destructive bulk actions.
- Visual guidance: subtle depth, crisp typography, high contrast in action areas (e.g., bulk actions, critical status changes), and restrained accents per the design system.

